                    <td width="436"><img src="illus/fusio_006.jpg" width="12" height="16"></td></tr>
                <tr><td width="68">&nbsp;</td>
                    <td width="436" class="texte">In-Fusio is a mobile games service provider who aims at providing a high-quality and satisfactory global gaming service to operators.<BR>Created in August 1998, it was the first to launch the concept of games for mobile phones. In-Fusio is today the European leader in downloadable games.<BR><BR>The In-Fusio's offer is consistent through:<BR><BR> . GAMEZILLA PLATFORM SERVICES: <BR>   -> Provide and operate Gamezilla platform in Application Service Provider mode.<BR><BR> . IN-FUSIO'S GAMES CATALOGUE:<BR>   -> Provide access to a continually updated and exciting games' portfolio.<BR><BR> . GAME CENTRE MANAGEMENT:<BR>   -> Stimulate traffic through animation of  the players' community with dedicated game centres; challenge players through contests; find prizes; display ranking of scores...<BR><BR>In-Fusio’s solution increases pleasure and confidence of end-users in mobile services, thus increasing connections, revenues, and loyalty. In-Fusio's service increases operators' ARPU by an average 8%!<BR><BR>The company has reinforced its position as world market leader thanks to its downloadable games, made possible with ExEn download gaming engine and Gamezilla platform. In-Fusio’s downloadable games reach an average penetration rate of 50% and  90% of end-users expressed satisfaction.<BR>Developed by In-Fusio, ExEn offers the very best video game interface for real time animated graphics and therefore is an obvious choice for many game categories. A wide range of ExEn games, written in Java(tm) by a growing community of developers, are downloaded from the Gamezilla platform. They are executed on ExEn enabled mobile phones, from entry-level phases to high-end devices.<BR><BR>Worldwide operators, manufacturers and game studios & publishers already trust In-Fusio.<BR>The company publishes today through worldwide  operators including D2 Vodafone, Orange France, SFR (Vodafone), Telefonica Moviles, Omnitel Vodafone, China Mobile, etc…. In addition, In-Fusio has partnerships with manufacturers, such as  Siemens, Sagem, Philips, and Trium (by Mitsubishi), game studios & publishers, such as Kaolink, Ulysseo, Iomo and Infraworld, and licensors, such as Universal. These partnerships ensure the very best video-like games adapted to all handsets. <BR><BR>The In-Fusio team is currently 101 people, covering a dozen nationalities, who have all joined to carry out the task of making this young company the world leader in Connected Mobile Games. The company's values are Fun, Respect, Confidence and Innovation. Combined with a strong team spirit, a large dose of company-wide ambition and clear individual missions, they guarantee that however hard they work, they all have a good time. <BR></td></tr>
